spanGrp.span: A man lived with his wife up far in the woods.
Tara jeyiwa je sr-g juape ra ke mapum jui k' digin
Their house was made of leaves.
ta jie-wa j yu-l r kagu wa
But one day there came a time when they had a child, a boy child.
Tara un dia tara jie-wa se-n' dem un tiempo tara jeska jie-wa yaba ta jie-wa yaba e-gla r jeyiwa
They talk about how the child would grow up and work;
jeska jie-wa ts kpag yaba yaba kebir-m yaba d-m keyege ra jir ken'w-m-ite
they lived well but they said, the man said to the woman,
Tara jie-wa sr-g bi tara jie-wa t sh-n jeyiyi sh alagl
lets go far, lets walk around the house!
shk shk mapum j pam shk
But lets leave the child sleeping at home.
Tara se t yaba mtan j n kp
We will come back in when he wakes up.
They went away and left the child at home.
They were in the forest and did not see that some deer came in the house and took the child along.
Jie-wa kajalali k' digin ka t sun-ra m due yabla de-w j n Je t yaba mnu-m/ mntse-m mntse-m
The child chased those deer well into the woods.
yaba t je due yabla tji-m tji-m kal digin kal digin mapum
the deer went away under the trees and left him alone.
(_) je due yabla mnu-lo-m kal digin t m'tan eglaua
There a huge snake grabbed him, rolled him up;
tara jeska mga keb t' t gug-w t pabutr-w
child thought it was his mother or his father.
Tara ee yaba t begets r mina o kaga yaba kaga
jeska (m) (_) keb ra jin Yaba jin'
talked to it and caressed it.
yaba kt keb ra yaba t due ee/ keb pasig
The snake threw the child down; so the child lied down and cried;
yaba yaba ji-w-n je keb t ra ka yaba ji/ (_) jk bagl-w ji'
the snake climbed up a tree, and because the child was crying so much, it came down and caressed him.
Tara jeskara keb keb mnka kaljula n y komo yaba ji-g (m) t' keb jk ji-te-n keb t pasig
Then his mother, the adults came back home and did not find the child; he was not sleeping.
Tara mina kegl-wa deu-lo-n Jeskara j n n t ka yaba kon t yaba yaba (_) yaba ka kun kp
His father looked for him under the trees and things.
yaba je yule-g kaga t (m) yul kal digin jir digin
He fought with the creatures, the wild dogs from the woods.
Bichi-wa ra n kb chichi ts k' digin je-wa (m) ra n kb
But he did not find the child.
Tara yaba t m oso dolon kw'
he thought it was his father; the child went away with the creature.
begets-ite kaga t/ kaga mnu-m yaba mnu-m (_) bichi ra
His father and mother looked for him but did not find him.
Tara mina-wa kaga-wa t yul ka kon
the child got lost; lets let him there!
